# 2. `HandoffServiceTest`

Very important now.

## Success case

```text
valid code
→ load handoff
→ load session
→ delete handoff
→ return response
```

## Failures

❌ invalid code
❌ expired code
❌ reused code
❌ missing session

---

## Example

```java
@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
class HandoffServiceTest {

    @InjectMocks
    private HandoffService service;

    @Mock
    private RedisLoginHandoffService handoffRedis;

    @Mock
    private RedisSessionService sessionRedis;

    @Test
    void shouldExchangeCode() {

        LoginHandoff handoff = new LoginHandoff();
        handoff.setSessionId("abc");

        UserSession session = new UserSession();
        session.setUserId("testuser");
        session.setUsername("testuser");

        when(handoffRedis.findByCode("123")).thenReturn(handoff);
        when(sessionRedis.findBySessionId("abc")).thenReturn(session);

        HandoffExchangeResponse response =
                service.exchange("123");

        assertEquals("testuser", response.getUserId());

        verify(handoffRedis).delete("123");
    }
}
```

